<HEADLINE>
China Ethnic Affairs Commission sends 2 mln yuan to Sichuan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 13 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
The State Ethnic Affairs Commission decided on Tuesday to grant 2
million yuan (about 285,000 U.S. dollars) to its provincial
branch in the southwestern Sichuan Province for disaster-relief
work.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used with a special focus on aiding ethnic
minorities who have been affected by the earthquake. The
organization will also mobilize all its employees to donate to
the disaster-hit areas.
</P>
<P>
Wenchuan County, which was the epicenter of the Monday quake
measuring 7.8 on the Richter scale, is located in the Aba
Autonomous Prefecture of Tibetan and Qiang nationalities, Sichuan
Province.
</P>
